⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of FINAL FANTASY
node FF1 · FF1 · ⟦FINAL FANTASY:FF1:84e8b1⟧

WHO   — FINAL FANTASY — the first light — the source of the line
WHAT  — The first Final Fantasy — the near-last gamble that became a dynasty: four blank-slate heroes, the four Orbs and their Fiends, the fallen knight Garland who becomes the demon Chaos, a paradox of time, and Nobuo Uematsu's first Prelude.
WHERE — the kingdom of Cornelia and a darkened world — four youths bearing four dimmed Orbs set out to restore the light and break a 2000-year loop  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy; the Light Warriors; the four Orbs; Garland; Chaos; the four Fiends  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — Four silent warriors carry four lightless crystals into a broken world, defeat its four elemental Fiends, and chase the demon Chaos back through a closed loop of time to its source.
HOW   — Crystallized from the original Final Fantasy (Square, Famicom 1987 / NES 1990).

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Carry four dead crystals into a dying world, kill its four Fiends, and break the loop that keeps remaking the demon at the root of time.

